Assigment: Prediction Assignment Writeup

In this project, our goal will be to use data from accelerometers on the belt, forearm, arm, and dumbell of 6 participants.

Executive Summary

Our preferred prediction model is a stacked one, using generalizaed lineal (GLM), linear discriminant (LDA), and boosting (GBM).

From the ytrain data we discarded those recvord marked as new_window = “yes”, those records represent statistics over a time window of simple metrics (new_window=“no”). The reason for this is that the Test dataset does not contains that kind of records. Several columns (“kurtosis_roll_dumbbell”, “max_roll_forearm”, “amplitude_yaw_forearm” , “kurtosis_yaw_dumbbell”) only make sense for those omitted recors, so we discard this columns too.

In several cases, particularly on class “A” captures, it seems that for the first few seconds the user is not performing the exercise, as we can count around 10 cycles on some variables starting in the midst of the recording.

That observation allows us to trim the training data discarding the first seconds of the recording in order to avoid training with data before the exercise is performed.

Nevertheless we didn’t needed to do that in order to obtain good quality predictions.

On preprocessing we : * found none zero nor near-zero variance variables, * found none variable wich is a linear combination of other variables * several variables with high linear correlation.

We checked principal component transformation, but found that transformation tend to emphasize difference between users rather than differences between classes (the data feed to the transformation did not included the username).

So we avoided the PCA transformation, an used the raw data, then excluding higly correlated variables.

We used a 8-fold cross-validation to estimate in-training accuracy.

Our prefered model uses stacking using LDA, GLM GBM models and the user_name variable, since we are convinced that particularities of the captured data make sense mostly between data from the same user.

Other models that completly ignore the user_name variable produced weaker predictions.

Our preferred model have an inner 8-fold accuracy of 0.998 (Kappa of 0.99595).

  • Note:
    • We will accept the model even with several warnings on potential colinearity since:
      • we droped variables with high correlation
      • the cross-validation accuracy is still high
    • So we migth have overfitting (or perfect predictions) on some cases but not in a scale that invalidate the prediction
    • On the other hand, we have 2402 cros-valitation test cases for 35 predictors, so we bet most likely it’s a good prediction and not overfitting.
    • The same goes for LDA
